     "Against ICE-BREAK / ICE-CRASH: those begin with a high-crest fracture transient and are far louder; MOVEMENT has no initiating event and a low root_mean_square_level.",
     "Against ICE-FRICTION: friction is continuous surface contact (low crest, sustained); movement is a train of discrete clatters.",
     "Against SNOW-MOVEMENT: the material axis again — snow movement is a dark, dense crunch; ice movement is a bright clatter."
